dcterms:description: The Rutgers dataset consists of link traces from 29 nodes at 5 different noise levels. The dataset contains the raw Received Signal Strength Indicator (RSSI), sequence numbers, source node ID, destination node ID and artificial noise levels. Each RSSI value represents the signal strength of a received packet sent every 100 milliseconds, for a period of 30 seconds.
dcterms:title: Rutgers dataset
